<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-862-778  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 862 778.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Sept 18 1989 v10 n37 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multimedia technology is good for the heart. (computer applicationto teach preventive medicine to beginning doctors)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mahnke, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The American Heart Association (AHA) offers a multimediainteractive computer program to medical students and beginningdoctors to teach them about the dangers of high cholesterol, atopic that is glossed over in the standard medical education.andP;  TheCholesterol Education Program fills a 20Mbyte hard disk with text,full-color graphics, sound and animation.andP;  The program runs onApple computers, but the AHA plan to release an IBM version by theend on 1990.andP;  The program will be sent free to 150 medicalstudents and offered to teaching hospitals to supplement a weakarea in the students' medical education.andP;  The program specificallyaddresses the hazards of high blood cholesterol levels, is justone part of an ongoing effort by the AHA to inform doctors,medical professionals and the general public about the importanceof cardiovascular health.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Cholesterol Education Program (Educational software) (educationaluse).andO;Topic:     American Heart AssociationMedical EducationInteractive SystemsUser InterfaceEducational Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>